## Farzana's Top 5 Three-Stone Settings for Pear Diamonds

**1. Pear Sidestone Diamond Engagement Ring ($1,820 / 63 reviews)** — The only setting in the Blue Nile configurable catalog with actual pear-shaped side stones. The 1/4ct total side stone weight is calibrated for 0.65–0.85ct centers. Start here for any oval-center-with-pear-sides configuration. Available in all three 14k gold metals.

**2. Marquise Cut Three Stone by James Allen ($1,970 / 152 reviews)** — The most-reviewed three-stone setting in the catalog, full stop. The marquise side stones create maximum elongation when paired with a pear center — two elongated fancy-cut shapes creating maximum directional momentum. Available in yellow, white, and rose gold.

**3. Classic Pear Shaped Sidestone Ring in Platinum ($4,750 / 41 reviews)** — The premium pear sidestone setting for larger centers (1.25ct+). The 1/2ct total side stone weight meets The Three-Stone Ratio for 1.5ct centers, and platinum ensures pear side stone prongs hold for decades of daily wear.

**4. Tapered Baguette Engagement Ring ($1,920 / 215 reviews)** — The most-reviewed setting of any kind in the catalog that accepts a pear center. Tapered baguette sides create an Art Deco linear frame for the pear center that maximizes the pear's distinctive silhouette contrast. 215 reviews is the highest buyer confidence number in the entire Blue Nile three-stone catalog.

**5. Trillion Three Stone in Rose Gold ($3,255 / 4 reviews)** — The most distinctive aesthetic option. Pear center + trillion sides in rose gold creates a botanical, organic ring that reads unlike any other combination. If uniqueness is the priority, this is the setting.

