## Two Stone Pear Diamond Ring (Toi et Moi)

The two-stone "toi et moi" ring pairs two diamonds without a center/side hierarchy. Two pear diamonds set side-by-side — sharing a prong or bezel between them — read as two equal stones in dialogue. Opposing tips (one pointing up, one pointing down) creates a yin-yang rotation. Parallel tips creates directional momentum, like two waves moving together.

The toi et moi configuration does not appear as a configurable setting in the Blue Nile design-your-own catalog. It is available through custom jewelry design or specialist vintage dealers. The closest Blue Nile approximation is the East-West Sidestone and Pavé settings ($1,840, 19 reviews), which orient the center stone horizontally and create a similar side-by-side visual weight.

---

## Five Stone Pear Diamond Ring

The five-stone pear ring extends the three-stone concept with two additional flanking stones — one on each outer edge — creating five diamonds in a linear graduated arrangement. The most coherent five-stone pear configuration uses five graduated pear diamonds from large (center) to small (outermost), creating a fan effect that the pear's directional shape amplifies.

Five-stone pear rings are not available as configurable settings in the Blue Nile design-your-own catalog. They are available through custom jewelry fabrication, pre-set rings in Blue Nile's completed ring section, or vintage and estate jewelry dealers. For buyers specifically seeking a five-stone pear, custom fabrication with five GIA-certified graduated pear diamonds produces the most cohesive result.

---

## Metal Guide for Three Stone Pear Diamond Rings

**Yellow gold three-stone pear ring:** The dominant choice for oval + pear side stone configurations at 880 monthly searches. Yellow gold creates a warm, vintage, Art Deco aesthetic that defines this combination in {{year}}. Apply the [Metal Multiplier Effect](/pear-shaped-diamond-ring) — an H-I color oval center in yellow gold saves $400–$900 versus the G you'd need in white gold.

**White gold three-stone pear ring:** Best when the pear side stones or center should read as visually distinct design elements. The neutral metal maximizes contrast between shapes. For a pear center with linear side stones (baguette, emerald), white gold is the cleanest backdrop.

**Rose gold three-stone pear ring:** The most romantic three-stone metal choice. The Trillion Three Stone at $3,255 in rose gold and the Petite Micropavé Trio at $1,765 in rose gold both create warm, cohesive combinations where the metal's warmth blends the three stones into a unified look.

**Platinum three-stone pear ring:** The most secure option for shaped side stones. Trillion, pear, and baguette side stones have vulnerable prong geometry — platinum's density holds prongs tighter over decades than 14k gold. For an engagement ring with shaped side stones worn daily for life, platinum pays for itself in long-term stone security. For the full case on platinum vs. white gold for a pear diamond ring, see the [pear diamond engagement ring guide](/pear-diamond-engagement-ring).

