## Final Verdict: Best Three Stone Pear Diamond Ring for Every Budget

**Under $3,000 total:** Lab 0.70ct pear (G-VS2, Ideal, ~$650) + Pear Sidestone in 14k yellow gold ($1,820). Total: ~$2,470. Real pear-shaped side stones, 63 reviews, yellow gold — the oval + pear gold combination at the lowest credible price point with correct Three-Stone Ratio.

**$4,000–$6,000 total:** Natural 1ct pear (G-VS2, GIA Ideal, ~$3,150) + Pear Sidestone in 14k yellow gold ($1,820). Total: ~$4,970. A GIA-certified natural 1ct pear with matching pear side stones in yellow gold — the definitive expression of the three-stone pear ring at the mid-budget level.

**$6,000–$10,000 total:** Natural 1ct pear (G-VS2, GIA Ideal, ~$3,150) + Tapered Baguette Three Stone in 14k white gold ($3,410). Total: ~$6,560. The Art Deco configuration — linear baguette sides creating maximum contrast with a pear center. The highest-review category per setting type in this tier.

**$10,000+:** Natural 1.5ct pear (G-VS2, GIA Ideal, ~$7,800) + Classic Pear Sidestone in platinum ($4,750). Total: ~$12,550. The flagship configuration: a large natural pear center flanked by larger pear side stones in platinum. The Three-Stone Ratio is optimally met; platinum ensures the pear prongs hold for life.

