## Frequently Asked Questions

### What is a three stone pear diamond ring?

A three stone pear diamond ring features one center stone and two side stones where the pear cut appears in at least one position. The pear can be the center stone flanked by baguette, marquise, trillion, or emerald sides — or the side stones flanking an oval, round, or cushion center. The orientation of pear side stones (The Mirror Rule: tips outward) is the most critical design decision in the category.

### How much does a three stone pear diamond ring cost?

Setting prices on Blue Nile range from **$1,765** (Petite Micropavé Trio) to **$7,630** (Tapered Baguette Platinum, 5/8ct sides). The most popular pear sidestone setting costs $1,820 in all 14k gold metals. Total ring cost from setting + center stone: lab 1ct pear solitaires start at ~$2,620; natural GIA 1ct three-stone pear rings start at ~$4,970.

### What is The Mirror Rule for pear side stones?

The Mirror Rule states that pear-shaped side stones must be set with their pointed tips facing outward — toward the band ends — not inward toward the center stone. Inward-pointing pear tips create visual tension and make the ring look as if two arrows are targeting the center. Outward-pointing tips create an open fanning frame. All Blue Nile pear sidestone settings follow The Mirror Rule by default in their standard orientation.

### What is the best setting for an oval diamond with pear side stones?

The [Pear Sidestone Diamond Engagement Ring in 14k Yellow Gold](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-4-ct-tw-item-192877?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ($1,820, 63 reviews) is the starting point. It is the only configurable setting in the Blue Nile catalog with actual pear-shaped side stones, and at 63 reviews it has the most real buyer feedback. For larger oval centers (1.25ct+), the [Classic Pear Sidestone in Platinum](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-pear-shaped-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-1-2-ct-tw-item-194314?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ($4,750, 41 reviews, 1/2ct sides) meets the Three-Stone Ratio for that size.

### What is the Three-Stone Ratio for pear diamond rings?

The Three-Stone Ratio is the guideline that combined side stone weight should be 30–40% of center stone weight. For a 1ct pear center: target 0.30–0.40ct total in side stones (0.15–0.20ct per side). The 1/4ct total side stone settings ($1,820) are calibrated for 0.65–0.85ct centers. The 1/2ct total settings ($4,750) are calibrated for 1.25–1.65ct centers. Going below 20% of center weight makes side stones look like accent pavé; going above 50% creates three equal-looking stones with no clear focal point.

### What is a pear and marquise diamond ring?

A pear and marquise diamond ring is a three-stone ring combining a pear center stone with two marquise-cut side stones — or a marquise center flanked by pear sides. Both the pear and marquise are elongated fancy cuts with at least one pointed end, creating maximum finger elongation in combination. The [Marquise Cut Three Stone by James Allen](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/marquise-cut-diamond-three-stone-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-by-james-allen-item-315107?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ($1,970, 152 reviews) is the most-reviewed version on Blue Nile.

### What is diamond ring with pear shaped side stones?

A ring where two pear-cut diamonds are used as the side stones flanking a center diamond — rather than the pear being the center. The Blue Nile "Pear Sidestone Diamond Engagement Ring" ($1,820, 63 reviews) is the primary setting in this category. Pear side stones work best with oval, round, or cushion centers, following The Mirror Rule (tips pointing outward).

### Can I use a pear diamond in any three-stone setting?

Most three-stone settings accept a pear center stone if the basket is large enough and the setting includes a V-prong or protected prong at the pointed tip. Settings with a V-prong at the tip are required to prevent the pointed end from chipping under impact. All settings in the tables in this guide are compatible with pear center diamonds. Verify tip protection with Blue Nile's customer support before ordering if the setting description is unclear.

### What is a cushion cut diamond with pear side stones?

A cushion center stone with pear-shaped side stones creates a contrasting three-stone design where the blocky cushion center is flanked by elongated, asymmetrical pear diamonds. The contrast between the cushion's square silhouette and the pear's teardrop creates a fashion-forward ring. Pear side stones for a cushion center should be narrower than for an oval center — approximately 50–60% of the cushion's diameter — to maintain the cushion's visual prominence.

### What is a pear and emerald cut diamond ring?

A pear and emerald cut ring combines the brilliant pear cut with the step-cut emerald cut in a three-stone configuration. In the most common version, an emerald center is flanked by outward-pointing pear side stones (pear sidestone settings). In the less common version, a pear center is flanked by emerald side stones — the [Three-Stone Emerald Cut Setting at $4,510](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-emerald-cut-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-5-8-ct-tw-item-203648?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (4 reviews) or the [Zac Zac Posen version at $3,460](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/zac-zac-posen-three-stone-emerald-cut-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-3-ct-tw-item-203528?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (9 reviews).

### What is a five stone pear diamond ring?

A five-stone pear diamond ring places five diamonds in a linear arrangement, with pear diamonds appearing as some or all five stones. The most coherent version uses five graduated pear diamonds descending in size from center outward, creating a fan effect. Five-stone pear rings are not available as configurable settings in the Blue Nile design-your-own catalog; they require custom fabrication or can be found in Blue Nile's pre-set ring inventory.

### What is a pear shaped diamond with trillion side stones?

A pear center stone flanked by two trillion-cut (triangular) side stones. Both the pear and trillion are non-rectangular stones with at least one acute angle — their combination creates an organic, botanical aesthetic that contrasts with more linear baguette or emerald side stone options. The [Trillion Three Stone in Rose Gold ($3,255)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-trillion-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-1-3-ct-tw-item-203662?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and [in Platinum ($3,840)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-trillion-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-1-3-ct-tw-item-192950?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) are the two Blue Nile options.

### What is the most reviewed three-stone setting for a pear diamond on Blue Nile?

The Tapered Baguette Diamond Engagement Ring ($1,920) has 215 reviews — the highest review count of any setting compatible with a pear center stone. Among three-stone settings specifically designed with shaped side stones, the Marquise Cut Three Stone by James Allen has 152 reviews at $1,970. For the pear sidestone category (pear diamonds as side stones), the Pear Sidestone Engagement Ring has 63 reviews at $1,820.

